#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:7
msgid "v2.9.7 — Feature Release (April 3, 2026)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:9
msgid "AI Assistant — CPRMV Legislation Provider"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:11
msgid ""
"`CprmvMcpProvider` added to the MCP registry. Connects to the CPRMV HTTP MCP "
"server at `acc.cprmv.open-regels.nl/mcp` using "
"`StreamableHTTPClientTransport` — a remote HTTP endpoint, not a subprocess. "
"Enabled via `CPRMV_MCP_ENABLED=true`; URL overridable via `CPRMV_URL`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:13
msgid ""
"Three tools exposed: `rules_rules__rule_id_path__get` (retrieve rules from "
"BWB, CVDR, or EU CELLAR by rule ID path), "
"`ref_ref__referencemethod___reference__get` (resolve rules by Juriconnect "
"reference), `celex_cellar_by_celex__celexid___language___format__get` (look "
"up EU CELLAR publications by CELEX id)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:15
msgid ""
"`config.cprmv` added to `Config`: `enabled` (`CPRMV_MCP_ENABLED`, default "
"`false`), `url` (`CPRMV_URL`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:17
msgid "AI Assistant — LDE Process Library Provider"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:19
msgid ""
"`LdeMcpProvider` added. Spawns a custom `lde-mcp` stdio subprocess (`src/mcp-"
"servers/lde/index.ts` in dev, `dist/mcp-servers/lde/index.js` in prod) that "
"connects directly to the LDE `lde_assets` PostgreSQL database. Enabled via "
"`LDE_MCP_ENABLED=true` and `LDE_DATABASE_URL`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:21
msgid ""
"Six tools: `bundle_list`, `bundle_get` (deployed BPMN bundles with forms, "
"documents, subprocesses, and DMN keys), `form_list`, `form_get` (full "
"Camunda Form JSON schema), `document_list`, `document_get` (zones and "
"bindings)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:23
msgid ""
"SSL handled by stripping `sslmode` from the connection URL and passing `ssl: "
"{ rejectUnauthorized: true }` to the pg `Pool` constructor directly — avoids "
"the pg-connection-string `sslmode=require` deprecation warning."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:25
msgid ""
"`config.lde` added to `Config`: `enabled` (`LDE_MCP_ENABLED`, default "
"`false`), `databaseUrl` (`LDE_DATABASE_URL`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:27
msgid "AI Assistant — LLM Provider Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:29
msgid ""
"`LlmProvider` interface introduced in `src/services/llm/LlmProvider.ts`. "
"Decouples the agentic loop from any specific SDK — `mcpChat.service.ts` has "
"no direct dependency on Anthropic or OpenAI. Provider-agnostic types: "
"`AgentMessage`, `AgentToolUse`, `AgentToolResult`, `LlmStreamParams`, "
"`LlmTurnResult`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:31
msgid ""
"`LlmRegistry` singleton maps model IDs to their owning provider. "
"`getAvailableModels()` returns only models from providers where `isAvailable"
"()` is `true`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:33
msgid ""
"`AnthropicLlmProvider` registered with three models: `claude-sonnet-4-"
"20250514`, `claude-opus-4-20250514`, `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001`. Enabled "
"when `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is set."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:35
msgid ""
"`OpenAILlmProvider` registered with `gpt-4o` and `gpt-4o-mini`. Enabled when "
"`OPENAI_API_KEY` is set."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:37
msgid ""
"`GET /v1/mcp/models` added — returns all available models with `providerId` "
"and `providerDisplayName`. Used by the frontend model selector dropdown."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:39
msgid ""
"`POST /v1/mcp/chat` body extended with `modelId: string` — required field; "
"returns `400 INVALID_REQUEST` when absent."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:41
msgid ""
"Frontend: model selector dropdown rendered below the subtitle in the AI "
"Assistant header. Hidden when only one model is available. First available "
"model pre-selected on mount."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:43
msgid "Caseworker Dashboard — Procesbibliotheek"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:45
msgid ""
"New `procesbibliotheek` section added to the Home tab for all tenants whose "
"`leftPanelSections.home` includes the entry (currently Utrecht, Amsterdam, "
"Rotterdam, Den Haag, Flevoland). Publicly accessible (`isPublic: true`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:47
msgid ""
"Fetches deployed BPMN bundles from the LDE public API (`VITE_LDE_API_URL/"
"bundles/public`). A dedicated `ldeApi` Axios instance is used — no Keycloak "
"`Authorization` header is sent. Cards show process name, `bpmnProcessId`, "
"status badge (WIP/Actief/Concept), role badge (Standalone/Subprocess), and "
"deployment date; expand to reveal forms, documents, DMN keys, and deployment "
"ID."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:49
msgid ""
"`ProcessBundle`, `BundleDeployedForm`, `BundleDeployedDocument` types "
"exported from `api.ts`. `VITE_LDE_API_URL` added to all env files and `vite-"
"env.d.ts`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:53
msgid "v2.9.6 — Enhancement (April 2, 2026)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:55
msgid "IOU — Gebruiksscenario indienen — UX improvements"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:57
msgid ""
"Sub-step number badges in step 6 (Concrete Example) changed from filled blue "
"circles (`bg-blue-600 rounded-full`) to slate rounded squares (`bg-slate-500 "
"rounded-md`), eliminating the visual collision with the section header "
"badges which share the same shape and colour. The size was reduced from `w-6 "
"h-6` to `w-5 h-5` to keep them visually subordinate to the section headers, "
"and `font-mono` applied so the counter numerals read as distinct from "
"section numbers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:59
msgid ""
"Step 6 now has a remove button per row — only rendered when more than one "
"step is present to prevent accidental full deletion. The button turns red on "
"hover to signal destructive intent."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:61
msgid ""
"Step 9 (Existing Materials) gains an optional file attachment zone below the "
"existing material checkboxes — drag-and-drop or file picker, any file type, "
"up to 5 files at 10 MB each."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:63
msgid "Backend — new endpoint"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:65
msgid ""
"`POST /v1/public/upload-file` added to `public.routes.ts`. Accepts a single "
"file of any type via `multipart/form-data` (field name `file`), uploads it "
"to the GitLab project uploads API using `GITLAB_TOKEN`, and returns the "
"GitLab-generated markdown reference (`{ success: true, data: { markdown } }`)"
". Uses a dedicated `uploadAny` multer instance without the image-only "
"`fileFilter` used by the `/feedback` route."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:67
msgid ""
"The `/use-case` submission remains plain JSON (`Content-Type: application/"
"json`). Attachments are pre-uploaded one-by-one via `POST /v1/public/upload-"
"file` before the issue is created; the returned markdown references are "
"appended as a `## Bijlagen · Attachments` section in the issue body. This "
"avoids a multer v2 `req.body` field-parsing failure that occurred when text "
"fields were submitted alongside files in `multipart/form-data` — text fields "
"arrived as `undefined` regardless of file presence."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:69
msgid "Backend — development noise fix"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:71
msgid ""
"`ExternalTaskWorker.asyncResponseTimeout` reduced to 5 000 ms when `NODE_ENV "
"!== 'production'` (was 20 000 ms). The long-poll window exceeded the TCP "
"keep-alive timeout on the network path between the local dev machine and the "
"remote Operaton VM, causing repeated `ECONNRESET` poll errors in the "
"development log. The worker still runs locally; only the poll window is "
"shortened."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cchangelog-roadmap.md:75
msgid "v2.9.5 — Feature Release (April 1, 2026)"
msgstr ""

